<h3><a name="journal">Journal Papers</a></h3>
<div class="secbody">
<ul>
  <li>J. Albrecht, R. Hwa, and G. E. Marai. The Chinese Room:
  Visualization and Interaction to Understand and Correct Ambiguous
  Machine Translation. <i>Computer Graphics Forum</i>, Vol. 28, No. 3.

  <li>J. Albrecht and R. Hwa, Regression
  for Machine Translation Evaluation at the Sentence Level. 
  <i>Machine Translations</i>. No. 22, vol.1-2. Draft available upon request.

  <li>K. Liu, W. Chapman, R. Hwa, and R. Crowley. 2007. <a href="http://www.cs.pitt.edu/~hwa/LiuEtAl_jamia_finaldraft.pdf">Heuristic
  Sample Selection to Minimize Reference Standard Training Set for a
  Part-of-Speech Tagger</a> (final draft version). <i>Journal of the
  American  Medical Informatics Association,</i> No. 14, Vol. 5.

  <li>T. Wilson, J. Wiebe, and R. Hwa. 2006. <a
  href="http://www.cs.pitt.edu/~hwa/ci06.pdf"> Recognizing Strong and Weak Opinion Clauses</a>. In <i>Computational
  Intelligence</i>.

  <li>R. Hwa, P. Resnik, A. Weinberg, C. Cabezas, and O. Kolak. <a
  href="http://www.cs.pitt.edu/~hwa/nle04draft.pdf">Bootstrapping
  Parsers via Syntactic Projection across 
  Parallel Texts</a>.  <i>Special Issue of the Journal of Natural Language
  Engineering on Parallel Texts</i>, Eds. Rada Mihalcea and Michel
  Simard. 11:3, pp. 311-325, 2005.
  <li>R. Hwa. <a
  href="http://www.cs.pitt.edu/~hwa/cldraft.pdf">Sample selection for
  statistical parsing.</a> <i>Computational Linguistics</i> 30:3, 2004.</li>
  <li>B. Dorr, N. Ayan, N. Habash, N. Madnani, and R. Hwa.  <a
  href="http://www.cs.pitt.edu/~hwa/TALIP03.pdf">Rapid Porting of DUSTer to Hindi</a>, <i>ACM Transactions on Asian Language Information 
    Processing (TALIP)</i>, 2:3, 2003.</li> 
  <li> N.F. Otani and R. Hwa. Topological considerations in the
  generation of scroll waves in excitable and cyclical
  media. <i>Physica D</i>, 77, pp 434-455, 1994.  (pdf
  unavailable)</li></ul>

</div> 

<h3><a name="conf">Refereed Conference and Workshop Papers</a></h3> 

<div class="secbody"> 

<ul> 
<li> H. Xue and R. Hwa. <b>2014</b>. Improved Correction Detection in Revised ESL Sentences. In The Proceedings of The 52nd Annual Meeting of the Association for Computational Linguistics (ACL short), 2014, Baltimore, Maryland.

<li>H. Xue and R. Hwa. 2014. Redundancy Detection in ESL Writings. In The Proceedings of the 14th Conference of the European Chapter of the Association for Computational Linguistics (EACL), Gothenburg, Sweden.

<li>H. Hashemi and R. Hwa. 2014. A Comparison of MT Errors and ESL Errors. In the Proceedings of the 9th edition of the Language Resources and Evaluation Conference (LREC-2014), Reykjavik, Iceland.

<li>P. Pham, J. Wiebe, R. Hwa, W. Chapman <b>2013</b>. Automated Annotation of Colonoscopy Reports. Poster presented at the 2013 AMIA Summit on Clinical Research Informatics (CRI 2013).

<li> S. Lu, Y. Ye, R. Tsui, X. Liu, R. Hwa. Feature Selection for 30-Day Heart Failure Read- mission Prediction Using Clinical Drug Data.  NIPS Workshop on Machine Learning for Clinical Data Analysis and Healthcare, 2013.

<li>A. Conrad, H. Hochheiser, W. Chapman, R. Hwa, and J. Wiebe. 2013. Tightly-Coupled Natural Language Processing and Visualization for Electronic Medical Record Chart Review. Poster presented at the 2013 AMIA Summit on Clinical Research Informatics (CRI 2013).

<li>H. Xue and R. Hwa. <b>2012</b>. Modeling ESL Word Choice Similarities By Representing Word Intensions and Extensions. Proceedings of the 24th International Conference on Computational Linguistics(COLING).

<li>A. Conrad, J. Wiebe, and R. Hwa. 2012. Recognizing Arguing Subjectivity and Argument Tags. ACL Workshop on Extra-propositional aspects of Meaning.

<li>M. Grabmair, K.D. Ashley, R. Hwa and
